text_blocks.snippet: Here is the breakdown of the surviving and recently deceased core members of The Beach Boys as of early 2026.

list.snippet: Mike Love
Age: 84 (born March 15, 1941).
Skills & Occupations: Lead vocalist, lyricist, and frontman.
Proficiency: Expert singer (nasal tenor/bass-baritone) and prolific songwriter/co-author of over a dozen Top 10 hits.
Current Residence: Primarily resides on the North Shore of Lake Tahoe, Nevada/California.
Al Jardine
Age: 83 (born September 3, 1942).
Skills & Occupations: Rhythm guitarist, vocalist (mid-range harmonies), and songwriter.
Proficiency: Highly proficient in folk-influenced rhythm guitar and complex vocal arrangements; occasionally sang lead on hits like "Help Me, Rhonda".
Current Residence: Longtime resident of Big Sur, California.
Bruce Johnston
Age: ~83 (born June 27, 1942).
Skills & Occupations: Keyboards, bass, vocals, and Grammy-winning songwriter.
Proficiency: Expert arranger and keyboardist; joined in 1965 to replace Brian Wilson on tour and famously wrote "I Write the Songs".
Current Residence: Primarily resides in Santa Barbara, California.
David Marks
Age: 77 (born August 22, 1948).
Skills & Occupations: Lead and rhythm guitarist, vocalist.
Proficiency: Professional-level guitarist who played on the band's first four albums.
Current Residence: Maintains a low profile in the Los Angeles, California area.
Brian Wilson
Status: Passed away at age 82 on June 11, 2025, in Beverly Hills, California.
Legacy: Widely considered a musical genius; he was the band's primary composer, producer, and bassist.
Dennis Wilson: Died December 1983 (Age 39); Drummer/Vocalist.
Carl Wilson: Died February 1998 (Age 51); Lead Guitarist/Vocalist.

references.title: Legendary Beach Boys co-founder Brian Wilson, whose music defined a generation and captured the California spirit, passed away at age 82 on June 11th. A musical genius behind classics like Good Vibrations and God Only Knows, Wilson’s influence transcended genres and generations. Today in Huntington Beach, fans, surfers, and loved ones gathered for an emotional paddle out ceremony, honoring his life, legacy, and deep connection to the ocean. We were there to capture the powerful tribute—waves of gratitude for a man who gave the world so much beauty through sound. Rest in peace, Brian. references.title: 45 years ago today, The Beach Boys released “Good Timin’”, the second single from their 1979 album L.A. (Light Albums). It’s one of the few songs credited to both Brian and Carl. The song reached the top 40 on the singles chart and No. 12 on the Billboard Adult Contemporary chart. Brian played piano, harpsichord and organ on the track. Side B was Dennis’ “Love Surrounds Me,” featuring backing vocals by Fleetwood Mac’s Christine McVie.
